The '''dhuryam''' was a [[Biot|bioengineered lifeform]] that was created by the [[Yuuzhan Vong]].

==Overview==
They were relatives of the [[yammosk]] war coordinators but were far larger and much more powerful as their duties entailed running all the organisms of a planet, making them world coordinators. At least thirteen such creatures were bred and were irreplaceable as they were trained with a single task which was to be fulfilled, which in turn led to them becoming the ''pazhkic Yuuzhan'tar al'tirrna'', or [[World Brain]].

One of them would manage the thousands of biological processes that would go into terraforming and maintaining [[Coruscant/Legends|Yuuzhan'tar]], the Yuuzhan Vong homeworld. Because the World Brain had to be of the highest quality, it was selected through a process called the ''[[tizo'pil Yun'tchilat]]'': the Day of Comprehending the Will of the Gods. All thirteen dhuryams were severed from their telepathic link with their slaves by the [[Shreeyam'tiz]], which were a smaller subspecies of the [[yammosk]] that existed only for that task. When one dhuryam remained, either from killing its siblings or by some other method, it assumed direct control over Yuuzhan'tar.

==History==
The World Brain was chosen by [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]] after he killed all twelve of the other dhuryams. Jacen convinced it to sabotage the [[Terraforming/Legends|Vongforming]] of Coruscant. As the war came to its closing stages, dhuryam governor brains were becoming increasingly scarce for the [[Yuuzhan Vong empire]].

The dhuryam remained after the [[Battle of Yuuzhan'tar]].

Years later, the dhuryam would again help Jacen Solo. During the [[Second Galactic Civil War]], Solo was appointed the leader of the [[Galactic Alliance Guard]]. He covertly used the World Brain to detect and round up [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] insurgents on Coruscant. When [[Alema Rar]] returned to Coruscant to exact revenge on the [[Solo family/Legends|Solo family]], she followed Jacen to the World Brain. When she attempted to kill him with a blowdart, [[Lumiya]], Jacen's [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] mentor, Force pushed him out of the way of Alema's attack and the dart instead hit the World Brain. The World Brain began to thrash violently. Jacen and Lumiya then began an attempt to save the World Brain. However, the World Brain succumbed to the toxins and Jacen was upset by the loss of his friend.

